1
00:00:15,363 --> 00:00:16,364
Make love...

2
00:00:16,416 --> 00:00:19,200
is an action of affirmation to show true love among two people.

3
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,040
I really don't want to go to Penang.

4
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:22,960
I think I will miss you so much.

5
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,441
Please wait for me,

6
00:00:24,557 --> 00:00:26,640
I will come back and make love to you every night.

7
00:00:27,797 --> 00:00:29,560
The Lord will come home in two days.

8
00:00:29,743 --> 00:00:32,463
Do you remember Tone, Soi's son, who used to work here?

9
00:00:32,590 --> 00:00:33,640
Did you get to meet him?

10
00:00:33,962 --> 00:00:36,063
I hired him to be Shen's personal driver.

11
00:00:36,103 --> 00:00:38,640
You're Lord Sampanpanich's wife and you need something to show, okay?

12
00:00:40,537 --> 00:00:43,120
But your husband is home now, it will get better, right?

13
00:00:43,423 --> 00:00:44,920
But since he got back

14
00:00:45,143 --> 00:00:46,520
he hasn't been the same.

15
00:00:46,663 --> 00:00:47,870
This is Shen, my wife.

16
00:00:48,697 --> 00:00:50,117
Nice to meet you, ma'am.

17
00:00:50,210 --> 00:00:52,560
This is Tone. He will be your personal driver.

18
00:00:55,717 --> 00:00:57,600
What are you doing? Don't do that.

19
00:00:57,703 --> 00:00:58,704
Make love...

20
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:00,680
You are the one who taught me this.

21
00:01:01,437 --> 00:01:03,600
- When you came back…
- Listen to me!

22
00:01:03,990 --> 00:01:04,991
It's my right.

23
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,201
And we will not talk about this anymore.

24
00:01:33,183 --> 00:01:34,184
Come on, kids.

25
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,200
Soi, where is Tone?

26
00:01:42,717 --> 00:01:44,543
He's sweeping leaves at the back of the house, sir.

27
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,960
- Tone.
- Mr. Perm.

28
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,200
You're back.

29
00:01:53,123 --> 00:01:54,360
How was your trip? Was it fun?

30
00:01:54,557 --> 00:01:57,360
So much fun. Here, I got something for you.

31
00:01:58,497 --> 00:01:59,498
Wow!

32
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:01,760
Look so yummy.

33
00:02:02,810 --> 00:02:03,811
Thank you, sir.

34
00:02:04,183 --> 00:02:06,960
This one is so good, you should try.

35
00:02:11,950 --> 00:02:14,000
You're right, it's good.

36
00:02:14,483 --> 00:02:17,000
You always bring me gifts from your trip.

37
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:19,320
It's because you're my friend.

38
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:30,680
Take a good care of him.

39
00:02:31,690 --> 00:02:33,400
I've raised him for years.

40
00:02:35,180 --> 00:02:36,381
I love him so much.

41
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,281
What about me? Do you love me?

42
00:02:47,430 --> 00:02:48,600
Why did you ask me that?

43
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:57,641
About last night,

44
00:02:58,757 --> 00:03:00,920
did you really expect me not to ask you anything?

45
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:07,600
Well, I'm sorry about last night.

46
00:03:08,497 --> 00:03:09,520
Listen, if you want anything,

47
00:03:10,243 --> 00:03:12,200
just let me know. I'll get it for you.

48
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:14,583
Do you think that what I really want

49
00:03:14,723 --> 00:03:16,960
are things, money and gold?

50
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:20,120
I really want your love.

51
00:03:20,177 --> 00:03:21,640
Do you think that I don't love you?

52
00:03:32,288 --> 00:03:33,720
I love you in my own way.

53
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:47,160
You will need to attend a ballroom dance class this afternoon.

54
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:51,880
There will be a dance party at my boss' palace next month, Prince Pin.

55
00:03:52,890 --> 00:03:54,160
I will take you there.

56
00:03:55,417 --> 00:03:56,418
Okay.

57
00:03:58,490 --> 00:03:59,920
Where do you want me to take the lesson?

58
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:03,240
Tone knows the address, he will take you this afternoon.

59
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:07,080
You need a dance partner for the class

60
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:09,720
so you should dance with him.

61
00:04:10,450 --> 00:04:11,451
I'm busy lately.

62
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:45,840
Is it okay that Mr. Perm wanted me to be your dance partner?

63
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,640
Well, he needed to work, didn't he?

64
00:04:49,690 --> 00:04:51,040
This is how it has to be.

65
00:04:57,977 --> 00:04:59,920
How are you legs?

66
00:05:00,930 --> 00:05:02,360
Are they still hurt from Khunying's punishment?

67
00:05:02,943 --> 00:05:03,944
Did you put some ointments on?

68
00:05:07,363 --> 00:05:08,200
I'm fine.

69
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,040
I can tolerate wounds on my legs.

70
00:07:25,297 --> 00:07:27,240
Well done. Excellent.

71
00:07:29,743 --> 00:07:30,744
Everyone,

72
00:07:31,003 --> 00:07:34,040
we have new students joining our class today.

73
00:07:34,543 --> 00:07:37,240
They are Shen and Tone.

74
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,161
Shen and Tone,

75
00:07:40,023 --> 00:07:42,000
this is Mr. Suthee, our dance instructor.

76
00:07:44,757 --> 00:07:46,720
You all should take a break

77
00:07:46,957 --> 00:07:48,840
and allow me to give our new students some dance lessons.

78
00:07:55,457 --> 00:07:59,240
Let's start with the beginning lesson.

79
00:08:00,158 --> 00:08:02,360
Can you step closer?

80
00:08:03,277 --> 00:08:05,120
Please take one more step

81
00:08:05,237 --> 00:08:06,240
towards each other, getting closer.

82
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:10,041
The male needs to show both of his palms up.

83
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,480
Then the female needs to put her palms down on his.

84
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,440
Shen, please hold his hands.

85
00:08:17,443 --> 00:08:18,445
Please do it.

86
00:08:19,842 --> 00:08:22,080
That's it, holding hands like that.

87
00:08:22,243 --> 00:08:25,440
Then the male will start the first step with his left leg.

88
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:27,277
It will be four steps which are

89
00:08:27,472 --> 00:08:29,783
left-right-left-touch.

90
00:08:30,030 --> 00:08:31,920
The female will need to walk backwards, following these steps

91
00:08:32,117 --> 00:08:33,960
right-left-right-touch.

92
00:08:34,130 --> 00:08:35,880
Then you will repeat the steps back and forth.

93
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,080
Got it? Let's try it first.

94
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:40,400
I'll start counting to four.

95
00:08:40,757 --> 00:08:44,758
One…two…three. Go!

96
00:08:45,037 --> 00:08:48,043
Step, step, step, touch and four.

97
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:52,040
Step, step, step and touch.

98
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:54,930
You need to be more natural.

99
00:08:55,090 --> 00:08:57,591
Don't be too stiff, relax your muscles.

100
00:08:58,610 --> 00:09:00,760
Look into each other's eyes, make eye contact.

101
00:09:01,177 --> 00:09:02,730
You need to look at your partner.

102
00:09:02,737 --> 00:09:04,360
I'll start counting again.

103
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:08,160
One…two…three, hold hands. Let's do it again.

104
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:11,960
One…two…three…four. Step.

105
00:09:12,067 --> 00:09:16,080
One…two…three…touch and four. Go!

106
00:09:16,223 --> 00:09:19,762
One…two…three…touch and four.

107
00:10:01,883 --> 00:10:02,884
What were you thinking?

108
00:10:03,183 --> 00:10:05,640
Why did you let your wife take a dance lesson with a driver?

109
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,121
How did you know about this?

110
00:10:10,570 --> 00:10:12,760
Rayrai's friend also took the same class.

111
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:17,560
Jintana stopped by and hung out with me this afternoon.

112
00:10:19,743 --> 00:10:22,080
Shen needed to take dance classes for prepare for social events.

113
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:23,360
I was busy

114
00:10:23,523 --> 00:10:25,760
so I asked Tone to be her dance partner. What's wrong with that?

115
00:10:26,123 --> 00:10:28,160
You let your wife hold hands with one of our servants

116
00:10:28,810 --> 00:10:30,000
and you thought that was normal?

117
00:10:31,017 --> 00:10:32,160
Have you ever loved your wife at all?

118
00:10:32,937 --> 00:10:35,920
If she was my wife, I wouldn't let her do that for sure.

119
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:37,400
Good thing that she wasn't your wife.

120
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:42,040
I trust both Shen and Tone

121
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,320
so I let them dance together.

122
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:48,120
What about the others' opinion? What would they think?

123
00:10:48,430 --> 00:10:49,560
Have you ever thought about that?

124
00:10:50,043 --> 00:10:51,760
It could ruin our family's reputation.

125
00:10:51,983 --> 00:10:54,640
Mom, in western culture,

126
00:10:54,690 --> 00:10:56,720
people who are dance partners

127
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,720
don't mean that they are doing some nasty things.

128
00:11:00,150 --> 00:11:02,280
Can you be a little bit more civilized like the rest of the world?

129
00:11:03,297 --> 00:11:05,760
Did you just call me barbaric?

130
00:11:06,450 --> 00:11:08,240
Well, slamming a table during dinner time

131
00:11:08,970 --> 00:11:10,600
doesn't consider as civilized either.

132
00:11:29,430 --> 00:11:31,520
Tone, be honest with me.

133
00:11:32,383 --> 00:11:35,480
Did Mr. Perm really let you take a dance lesson with his wife?

134
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,243
That's right, auntie.

135
00:11:37,823 --> 00:11:38,824
This is strange.

136
00:11:39,323 --> 00:11:41,760
Normally, husbands will be possessive of his wife over thing like this.

137
00:11:42,217 --> 00:11:44,280
In Mr. Perm's case,

138
00:11:44,383 --> 00:11:45,720
he is more open-minded than the ocean.

139
00:11:46,717 --> 00:11:49,760
Mr. Perm said that he trusted his wife and Tone.

140
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,160
Why are you still questioning about this?

141
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,201
- What?
- Yeah.

142
00:11:52,401 --> 00:11:53,602
One more thing,

143
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:56,960
Mr. Perm loves his wife so much.

144
00:11:57,223 --> 00:12:00,600
You never loved someone, you wouldn't understand.

145
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,600
What? How did you know? Huh?

146
00:12:04,937 --> 00:12:05,938
Tone.

147
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:08,751
I saw it that when two people were dancing,

148
00:12:09,110 --> 00:12:11,000
they were getting so close like this.

149
00:12:11,677 --> 00:12:14,100
Did you and Ms. Shen get so close like that too?

150
00:12:14,803 --> 00:12:17,577
Shin, can you stop with your disgusting questions?

151
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:21,360
We were not that close, there is plenty of space between us.

152
00:12:21,483 --> 00:12:23,703
Yeah…right. Plenty of space, huh?

153
00:12:24,077 --> 00:12:25,457
You said it as if there was a huge space between the two of you.

154
00:12:26,557 --> 00:12:29,500
When you danced with Ms. Shen,

155
00:12:29,883 --> 00:12:31,320
did you feel anything?

156
00:12:31,370 --> 00:12:32,840
Shin, you a--hole.

157
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,240
I told you to stop asking me disgusting questions.

158
00:12:35,923 --> 00:12:37,240
This could taint Ms. Shen's reputation.

159
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:40,520
Fine, whatever you say.

160
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:43,100
Mr. Perm has always trusted you since you were a kid.

161
00:12:45,177 --> 00:12:47,550
- That was so loud.
- You deserved it.

162
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:56,200
Tone, you see her?

163
00:12:56,637 --> 00:12:59,257
She is Ms. Daeng, Chaokhun Direk's daughter.

164
00:12:59,277 --> 00:13:01,960
That's right. Can you give her this necklace?

165
00:13:02,143 --> 00:13:03,360
And tell her that it is from me.

166
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:08,400
You like her, why don't you give it to her yourself?

167
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:12,400
I'm shy, that's why. Come on, give it to her

168
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,360
before her dad takes her home.

169
00:13:23,170 --> 00:13:24,171
Ms. Daeng,

170
00:13:25,171 --> 00:13:26,700
Mr. Perm asked me to give you the necklace.

171
00:13:30,703 --> 00:13:33,704
It's cute. Please say thank you for me.

172
00:13:34,357 --> 00:13:35,358
Wait.

173
00:13:36,757 --> 00:13:38,920
Can you put it on for me? I can't do it by myself.

174
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,760
Mr. Perm only asked me to give you the necklace.

175
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:44,520
He didn't tell me to put it on you.

176
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:49,160
Can you keep me company?

177
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:52,120
My dad is working and it's taking too long.

178
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:56,921
I'm sorry.

179
00:13:57,063 --> 00:13:58,920
I can't do more than he asked me to.

180
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,250
Excuse me.

181
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,961
How was it?

182
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:09,600
She said thank you.

183
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,201
Excellent.

184
00:14:11,297 --> 00:14:14,320
I can trust you with this kind of task.

185
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:16,440
Don't tell anyone

186
00:14:16,703 --> 00:14:18,760
- that I stole my mom's necklace.
- What?

187
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:31,041
Honey?

188
00:14:34,210 --> 00:14:37,160
Should we take a dance lesson on weekend?

189
00:14:37,703 --> 00:14:39,122
So I could learn it with you.

190
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:40,640
What's wrong with learning with Tone?

191
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:43,480
It seemed inappropriate like what your mom said.

192
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:44,791
I'm busy.

193
00:14:46,103 --> 00:14:47,680
Just take a lesson with Tone, it should be fine.

194
00:14:49,403 --> 00:14:51,880
Don't skip a class, you need to know how to dance.

195
00:14:52,297 --> 00:14:54,800
There will be good dancers attending the party at Prince Pin's palace.

196
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:58,120
I will find a seamstress to make you a dress.

197
00:15:02,817 --> 00:15:03,818
Honey?

198
00:15:11,583 --> 00:15:12,584
What now?

199
00:15:13,237 --> 00:15:14,560
Rehearse the dance.

200
00:15:15,397 --> 00:15:16,800
Please rehearse the dance with me.

201
00:15:17,130 --> 00:15:18,480
You need to do it yourself, I already know how to dance.

202
00:15:27,196 --> 00:15:28,640
How was it yesterday? Did you start to know how to dance?

203
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,300
Sure, I did.

204
00:15:30,323 --> 00:15:32,480
Hello, Jintana and Santi.

205
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:34,584
How are you?

206
00:15:35,163 --> 00:15:37,120
Are you Jintana, Rayrai's friend?

207
00:15:37,263 --> 00:15:38,603
I…that's right.

208
00:15:39,597 --> 00:15:41,520
Rayrai just mentioned you yesterday.

209
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,440
Nice to finally meet you.

210
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:48,561
Sure.

211
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,001
Since you've known how to move your feet,

212
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:57,840
he needs to put his hand on your waist.

213
00:15:59,709 --> 00:16:00,710
What did you say?

214
00:16:01,056 --> 00:16:03,200
Put his hand on your waist.

215
00:16:04,356 --> 00:16:06,040
Can't we just hold hands?

216
00:16:06,189 --> 00:16:08,720
It's just a dance lesson, we're not at a party.

217
00:16:08,857 --> 00:16:11,160
We need to rehearse it like we are actually in a party.

218
00:16:11,317 --> 00:16:13,960
If you don't know how to put your hands,

219
00:16:14,057 --> 00:16:15,840
your moves won't look nice.

220
00:16:16,197 --> 00:16:17,200
Let's just try.

221
00:16:23,130 --> 00:16:24,078
Excuse me.

222
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:47,800
Don't touch me there! I'm ticklish.

223
00:16:49,470 --> 00:16:50,280
I'm sorry.

224
00:17:02,930 --> 00:17:04,440
Then you need to

225
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:08,400
slowly put your hand on his shoulder like this.

226
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:12,240
And both of you hold these hands like this.

227
00:17:25,417 --> 00:17:26,418
That's right.

228
00:18:17,842 --> 00:18:19,520
You can't even dance properly by yourself.

229
00:18:20,050 --> 00:18:22,560
Won't you step on people's feet at the party?

230
00:18:23,137 --> 00:18:24,680
I am rehearsing my moves.

231
00:18:24,903 --> 00:18:26,700
I will get better on that day.

232
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:31,920
It is more than just dancing at the dance party,

233
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,540
but it is a way to socialize for aristocrats.

234
00:18:36,403 --> 00:18:37,880
A clumsy Chinese girl like you,

235
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,720
people will laugh at you at the party for sure.

236
00:18:43,123 --> 00:18:45,160
Aristocrats like to laugh at other people?

237
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:48,040
Did you talk back to me?

238
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:53,120
So I would know how to behave.

239
00:19:10,930 --> 00:19:11,931
Ms. Rayrai?

240
00:19:13,190 --> 00:19:14,191
Ms. Rayrai?

241
00:19:16,803 --> 00:19:18,240
Breakfast is ready.

242
00:19:31,650 --> 00:19:34,120
Ms. Rayrai. Are you okay?

243
00:19:45,310 --> 00:19:46,520
How is she?

244
00:19:47,077 --> 00:19:48,720
Is everything okay?

245
00:19:49,890 --> 00:19:52,680
Are you going to tell them or should I?

246
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,360
Mom, you're about to have a grandchild.

247
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,560
What? Your wife is pregnant?

248
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:01,590
She is 3-month pregnant.

249
00:20:02,083 --> 00:20:04,230
But it is her first pregnancy so it didn't show much.

250
00:20:06,417 --> 00:20:08,120
Shin, get the orange.

251
00:20:08,510 --> 00:20:10,400
She is pregnant so she must crave something sour.

252
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,823
- Thank you so much.
- No problem.

253
00:20:13,041 --> 00:20:14,720
Excuse me, I need to go and see her.

254
00:20:14,803 --> 00:20:15,804
Sure.

255
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,160
Come on, follow me.

256
00:20:23,537 --> 00:20:24,538
May I?

257
00:20:29,583 --> 00:20:30,584
Perm,

258
00:20:31,050 --> 00:20:32,681
aren't you happy for me?

259
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:35,320
It is my first child

260
00:20:36,337 --> 00:20:37,680
and the first niece or nephew of this house.

261
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:40,480
Sure, I'm happy for you.

262
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,640
Excuse me, doctor.

263
00:20:44,210 --> 00:20:45,520
- Okay.
- Chan, give him a ride back.

264
00:20:47,517 --> 00:20:49,560
Right...

265
00:20:51,170 --> 00:20:54,171
I heard that you were back from your official duty in Penang, didn't you?

266
00:20:54,743 --> 00:20:57,320
That's right. I've been back for a while.

267
00:20:58,243 --> 00:21:00,160
My friend is an English doctor,

268
00:21:00,343 --> 00:21:01,440
he also practices in Penang.

269
00:21:01,757 --> 00:21:03,120
His name is Dr. Trevor Smith.

270
00:21:03,610 --> 00:21:05,440
Have you seen him?

271
00:21:07,042 --> 00:21:10,120
I'm not sick, why would I need to go and see him?

272
00:21:10,297 --> 00:21:11,298
I see.

273
00:21:11,757 --> 00:21:14,920
Well, there must be so many Thai government officers working there.

274
00:21:15,363 --> 00:21:17,960
He sent me a letter and told me that

275
00:21:18,090 --> 00:21:21,920
one of his patients was Thai government officer.

276
00:21:22,163 --> 00:21:23,840
I thought that it was you.

277
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,241
It wasn't me.

278
00:21:27,317 --> 00:21:30,000
Did he tell you about the treatment given to them?

279
00:21:32,150 --> 00:21:33,151
He didn't tell me.

280
00:21:33,697 --> 00:21:35,320
It would violate his code of conduct.

281
00:21:35,943 --> 00:21:38,400
We just talked about this and that, nothing in details.

282
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,920
I'm glad that you're healthy.

283
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,271
See you later.

284
00:21:58,503 --> 00:21:59,504
Honey?

285
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,001
Honey!

286
00:22:06,590 --> 00:22:08,400
Should we go and see Rayrai upstairs?

287
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:13,441
No, but you should go.

288
00:22:15,343 --> 00:22:16,344
Okay.

289
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,200
- Tone.
- Yes, ma'am?

290
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,601
I need something to drink.

291
00:22:44,110 --> 00:22:45,111
Sure.

292
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:47,721
Thank you.

293
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:50,401
Ms. Shen, here.

294
00:22:50,530 --> 00:22:51,531
Thanks.

295
00:22:57,197 --> 00:22:59,360
So, are you beginning to like dancing?

296
00:23:02,937 --> 00:23:03,938
What did you say?

297
00:23:05,640 --> 00:23:08,840
You wanted me to teach you English, so I asked

298
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,480
Are you beginning to like dancing?

299
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:14,161
Are you beginning to like dancing?

300
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:18,121
Yes.

301
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:19,601
Little.

302
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:23,121
A little bit.

303
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:29,000
A little bit.

304
00:23:29,290 --> 00:23:30,291
Bit

305
00:23:30,537 --> 00:23:31,538
Bit

306
00:23:32,197 --> 00:23:33,198
A little bit.

307
00:23:33,230 --> 00:23:34,231
A little bit.

308
00:23:35,810 --> 00:23:36,811
A little bit.

309
00:23:45,103 --> 00:23:46,760
The shoulders' length is 14 inches.

310
00:23:49,070 --> 00:23:51,071
The arms' length is 23 inches.

311
00:23:55,140 --> 00:23:57,680
I guess 'fine feathers make fine birds'

312
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:00,720
can't be applied with everyone.

313
00:24:47,170 --> 00:24:48,760
What do you think of this gown?

314
00:24:51,240 --> 00:24:53,720
Not bad. Is it fit you well?

315
00:24:55,137 --> 00:24:56,920
It's a little tight on my hips,

316
00:24:57,123 --> 00:24:58,480
I need to get it altered.

317
00:25:01,857 --> 00:25:04,600
Why don't you put on your outfit?

318
00:25:05,050 --> 00:25:06,280
We can see if they will go well together.

319
00:25:06,423 --> 00:25:07,840
No need to, I'm too lazy to try it on.

320
00:25:22,777 --> 00:25:23,840
It's not good?

321
00:25:25,670 --> 00:25:27,100
You can order another one.

322
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:29,561
It's fine.

323
00:25:30,317 --> 00:25:31,318
It tastes good.

324
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:39,960
Are you okay?

325
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,441
Talk to me.

326
00:25:45,410 --> 00:25:46,411
What?

327
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:49,440
I said 'Talk...'

328
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:52,960
to me…'

329
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:54,800
Talk to me.

330
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:57,161
You can tell me.

331
00:26:04,417 --> 00:26:06,000
I just feel like

332
00:26:07,597 --> 00:26:09,280
it's hard to have

333
00:26:10,120 --> 00:26:11,360
everything so perfect all the time.

334
00:26:14,837 --> 00:26:18,200
What do you mean by 'everything?'

335
00:26:20,250 --> 00:26:21,440
Everything in this world.

336
00:26:22,937 --> 00:26:23,938
Including people.

337
00:26:31,090 --> 00:26:33,160
Are you talking about Mr. Perm?

338
00:26:39,903 --> 00:26:42,640
I don't know what's going on between both of you,

339
00:26:45,157 --> 00:26:46,880
but I can say that

340
00:26:47,030 --> 00:26:48,720
Mr. Perm loves you so much.

341
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:52,120
He can do everything in his power to make you happy.

342
00:26:56,170 --> 00:26:57,760
He can't do everything.

343
00:27:07,443 --> 00:27:11,720
If that so, is there anything I can do on his behalf?

344
00:27:12,997 --> 00:27:14,520
You can let me know.

345
00:27:17,290 --> 00:27:18,560
I will do it for you.

346
00:27:26,297 --> 00:27:27,600
There is something you can't do on his behalf.

347
00:27:29,937 --> 00:27:32,400
Let's eat, we have a dancing class to attend.

348
00:28:34,057 --> 00:28:35,458
- Here's some water, ma'am.
- Thanks.

349
00:29:53,197 --> 00:29:54,720
It was such exhausted like crazy today.

350
00:29:55,860 --> 00:29:58,720
But it's crazy fun too.

351
00:30:04,820 --> 00:30:05,821
Ms. Shen.

352
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:11,640
Should we visit the rice field before going back?

353
00:30:13,082 --> 00:30:14,183
We can rest for a while.

354
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:19,081
I don't think so.

355
00:30:19,330 --> 00:30:21,760
I'm afraid my husband will be worried about me when he gets home.

356
00:30:22,770 --> 00:30:24,480
But he has a meeting today.

357
00:30:26,377 --> 00:30:27,840
He should be home late.

358
00:30:58,703 --> 00:30:59,704
It's so windy out here.

359
00:31:02,903 --> 00:31:04,240
So much cooler than the weather at home.

360
00:31:17,123 --> 00:31:19,160
What type of dance do you like?

361
00:31:21,337 --> 00:31:24,360
Well, I like…

362
00:31:24,863 --> 00:31:25,962
I like…wal.

363
00:31:29,397 --> 00:31:30,398
Waltz.

364
00:31:32,543 --> 00:31:33,544
What did you say?

365
00:31:34,550 --> 00:31:35,551
Waltz.

366
00:31:37,597 --> 00:31:38,598
Waltz?

367
00:31:40,657 --> 00:31:41,658
Waltz.

368
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:43,681
What about you?

369
00:31:44,763 --> 00:31:46,440
I like it fast like

370
00:31:46,577 --> 00:31:47,960
swing or guaracha.

371
00:31:50,483 --> 00:31:53,040
Why do you like 'waltz'?

372
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:58,120
I like 'waltz….'

373
00:31:58,370 --> 00:31:59,371
That's right.

374
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:02,320
because….

375
00:32:04,180 --> 00:32:05,581
I feel free when I dance.

376
00:32:07,723 --> 00:32:10,000
I feel like I am a bird.

377
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:12,681
I can fly.

378
00:32:14,083 --> 00:32:16,160
I can fly to any places.

379
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:20,801
Like that.

380
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:38,401
I wish I could fly.

381
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:11,520
Are you okay?

382
00:33:14,677 --> 00:33:15,678
Ms. Shen.

383
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:19,960
I think you should rest in the cottage.

384
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:23,760
Easy and slowly.

385
00:33:35,083 --> 00:33:36,084
Be careful.

386
00:33:42,503 --> 00:33:44,000
Please wait a second.

387
00:34:05,137 --> 00:34:07,080
This oil can help with muscle tension.

388
00:34:18,177 --> 00:34:19,360
May I?

389
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:36,001
Is it hurt?

390
00:34:36,530 --> 00:34:37,531
Just a little bit.

391
00:34:37,883 --> 00:34:39,000
I'm sorry.

392
00:34:46,937 --> 00:34:50,240
Did you carry this type of oil in the car?

393
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:52,601
That's right, ma'am.

394
00:34:53,183 --> 00:34:55,040
I see that we dance every day,

395
00:34:55,677 --> 00:34:57,280
and we could need it when we have problems with our muscles.

396
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:00,560
The oil can help releasing muscle tension.

397
00:35:09,560 --> 00:35:10,561
Is it still hurt?

398
00:35:11,437 --> 00:35:12,438
I'm fine.

399
00:35:16,563 --> 00:35:19,000
You said that you was fine

400
00:35:19,070 --> 00:35:20,360
but it was the same tone as when you were hurt.

401
00:35:28,683 --> 00:35:30,280
Where did you learn about the massage?

402
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:33,000
My mom has muscle problem.

403
00:35:34,337 --> 00:35:36,440
I used to give her massage all the time.

404
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:54,360
Are you tired?

405
00:35:56,303 --> 00:35:57,960
You can take a nap if you want.

406
00:35:58,283 --> 00:36:01,122
You didn't rest today. I'll prepare you a bed.

407
00:36:14,310 --> 00:36:15,311
There, I'm done.

408
00:36:39,170 --> 00:36:41,417
I should continue my massage.

409
00:39:47,477 --> 00:39:48,478
Are you up?

410
00:39:48,843 --> 00:39:49,844
Yeah.

411
00:39:50,499 --> 00:39:52,600
What did you do? Why did your hair get all wet?

412
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:54,617
I was sweaty.

413
00:39:54,910 --> 00:39:57,400
I walked to the back of the house and I saw a big jar.

414
00:39:57,850 --> 00:39:59,680
So I took a shower.

415
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:01,881
I feel so refreshing now.

416
00:40:03,610 --> 00:40:05,280
You should be more careful next time.

417
00:40:09,723 --> 00:40:11,520
How were your feet?

418
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:14,480
Much better now. Let's go home.

419
00:40:37,896 --> 00:40:38,897
Follow me this way.

420
00:40:39,823 --> 00:40:41,440
Please wait here.

421
00:40:41,637 --> 00:40:43,441
- I will get Ms. Shen for you.
- Okay.

422
00:40:44,370 --> 00:40:45,371
No need to.

423
00:40:48,203 --> 00:40:49,204
Khunying?

424
00:40:49,323 --> 00:40:50,360
Is her gown finished?

425
00:40:50,943 --> 00:40:53,320
That's right. I altered the hips for her.

426
00:40:53,403 --> 00:40:56,560
She will be the most beautiful lady in the party for sure.

427
00:40:58,050 --> 00:40:59,720
- Shin, get the gown.
- Yes, ma'am.

428
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:04,921
Thank you so much.

429
00:41:05,650 --> 00:41:08,000
I will give it to Shen myself. You can leave now.

430
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:12,800
It's alright. You can go.

431
00:41:13,843 --> 00:41:14,844
Okay.

432
00:41:25,394 --> 00:41:26,920
Unwrap the gown for me.

433
00:41:27,337 --> 00:41:28,338
Yes, ma'am.

434
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:38,361
It's beautiful.

435
00:41:40,750 --> 00:41:42,800
But I think it can be even more beautiful than this.

436
00:41:58,650 --> 00:42:00,200
Are you almost done? What took you so long?

437
00:42:03,623 --> 00:42:04,657
Almost done.

438
00:42:26,170 --> 00:42:28,400
This is for you. So you would look more like a lady.

439
00:42:31,200 --> 00:42:32,920
- What is this?
- Just open it.

440
00:42:48,077 --> 00:42:51,040
Is this for me?

441
00:42:51,457 --> 00:42:54,040
You can wear it to the party and blend in with the others.

442
00:42:57,963 --> 00:42:58,964
Come in.

443
00:43:04,737 --> 00:43:05,920
Your gown is here, ma'am.

444
00:43:06,560 --> 00:43:09,360
The seamstress delivered it since morning but Khunying received it for you.

445
00:43:12,290 --> 00:43:14,920
I will put it on.

446
00:43:15,863 --> 00:43:18,280
It will go well with the pearl set you just gave me.

447
00:43:42,423 --> 00:43:44,120
Who received it for her?

448
00:43:48,243 --> 00:43:50,040
Shen! Shen!

449
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:55,400
Plaikaew said that…

450
00:43:58,723 --> 00:43:59,724
Mother!

451
00:44:01,606 --> 00:44:03,080
What happens, Shen?

452
00:44:03,817 --> 00:44:05,920
I think there is an animal running around in the house.

453
00:44:07,203 --> 00:44:08,204
Look at this.

454
00:44:08,377 --> 00:44:10,120
It bit my gown and it is ruined.

455
00:44:10,397 --> 00:44:12,240
If any of you sees it, you need to hit it hard.

456
00:44:12,723 --> 00:44:16,040
So it won't destroy your belongings or bite anyone.

457
00:44:17,274 --> 00:44:18,440
- Hey!
- Mom!

458
00:44:20,043 --> 00:44:22,244
Look at your wife! She can't talk to me like that.

459
00:44:22,557 --> 00:44:24,480
Mom, she didn't mention anyone.

460
00:44:27,520 --> 00:44:28,521
You're right.

461
00:44:29,970 --> 00:44:31,600
But your gown was ruined already.

462
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:34,721
I don't think you can attend the party tonight.

463
00:44:35,830 --> 00:44:36,840
Yes, I can.

464
00:44:37,560 --> 00:44:39,200
I still have my gowns in the closet.

465
00:44:40,050 --> 00:44:41,051
What gown?

466
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:45,040
You have the nice gowns to represent Pipatratsada family as an in-law?

467
00:44:45,800 --> 00:44:47,040
You can see it yourself.

468
00:45:29,440 --> 00:45:30,441
Shen!

469
00:45:34,430 --> 00:45:35,431
Get changed, now!

470
00:45:36,337 --> 00:45:38,280
Your dress is too scandal, like you're going to join a Chinese opera.

471
00:45:38,650 --> 00:45:40,960
I won't let you wear this dress when you're accompanying my son.

472
00:45:41,051 --> 00:45:42,252
This is so embarrassing.

473
00:45:42,497 --> 00:45:43,600
What can we do, Mom?

474
00:45:44,183 --> 00:45:46,040
Her western style gown was completely ruined.

475
00:45:48,250 --> 00:45:51,520
I think she also looks good in this dress.

476
00:45:52,903 --> 00:45:54,520
And you don't have to be embarrassed for me.

477
00:45:54,983 --> 00:45:57,350
I am the one taking her to the party, not you.

478
00:45:59,717 --> 00:46:00,480
Let's go.

479
00:46:05,903 --> 00:46:06,904
Hey!

480
00:46:14,143 --> 00:46:16,360
Mom! Why did you do that?

481
00:46:16,990 --> 00:46:18,700
To protect the family's reputation,

482
00:46:19,040 --> 00:46:20,520
I can be more violent than this.

483
00:46:29,640 --> 00:46:31,000
Don't mind her, let's go.

484
00:46:32,800 --> 00:46:35,560
Perm! Come back here.

485
00:46:35,890 --> 00:46:36,891
Perm!

486
00:46:37,360 --> 00:46:38,761
- To Nimman Palace.
- Got it, sir.

487
00:47:18,750 --> 00:47:19,751
Keep smiling.

488
00:47:48,623 --> 00:47:50,640
He is Prince Pinpreeda, the owner of this palace.

489
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:53,240
He is the head of commerce ministry, where I work.

490
00:47:54,840 --> 00:47:56,680
We are so grateful for him,

491
00:47:57,017 --> 00:47:58,560
he has taken care of our family, including my father and me.

492
00:47:59,680 --> 00:48:01,557
A lady who is sitting next to him

493
00:48:01,803 --> 00:48:04,200
is his youngest daughter, Khunying Anongnuch.

494
00:48:06,583 --> 00:48:07,584
I will introduce you to him.

495
00:48:14,450 --> 00:48:15,760
Hello, Perm.

496
00:48:16,517 --> 00:48:17,518
Good evening, sir.

497
00:48:21,200 --> 00:48:24,001
Don't be too formal, have a seat.

498
00:48:30,317 --> 00:48:31,700
Is this your wife?

499
00:48:34,050 --> 00:48:36,651
That's right, her name is Shen.

500
00:48:37,210 --> 00:48:39,920
I'd like to introduce her to you, Your Highness.

501
00:48:40,737 --> 00:48:41,738
Shen?

502
00:48:41,817 --> 00:48:44,240
You are good-looking and your dress is pretty.

503
00:48:44,717 --> 00:48:46,480
You picked the right one, well done.

504
00:48:48,760 --> 00:48:51,700
Nuch, you should say hi to her.

505
00:48:51,783 --> 00:48:53,600
You two are the same age, I think.

506
00:49:01,577 --> 00:49:05,160
You shouldn't spend time talking to an old folk like me. Go there.

507
00:49:05,277 --> 00:49:08,610
Find something for your wife to eat and hang out with people your age.

508
00:49:09,273 --> 00:49:11,611
It will be dancing session later.

509
00:49:12,123 --> 00:49:13,560
You can't miss it.

510
00:49:14,063 --> 00:49:15,430
I won't, Your Highness.

511
00:49:18,370 --> 00:49:20,400
You should get to know other people.

512
00:49:21,440 --> 00:49:23,320
You will need to attend the social events all the time.

513
00:49:24,023 --> 00:49:25,024
Got it, honey.

514
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:27,640
- Perm.
- Hi, Noppon.

515
00:49:28,130 --> 00:49:30,680
Sombat, how long have you been here?

516
00:49:30,803 --> 00:49:32,537
I finished two glasses already.

517
00:49:32,790 --> 00:49:34,200
Why did you just get here?

518
00:49:34,830 --> 00:49:36,720
I was busy helping Shen get ready.

519
00:49:40,160 --> 00:49:41,840
Where are your wives? Are they here?

520
00:49:42,037 --> 00:49:45,080
They're here. They're hanging out in the room over there.

521
00:49:45,640 --> 00:49:48,300
Why don't you bring your wife to meet them?

522
00:49:49,680 --> 00:49:50,681
I will be right back.

523
00:49:55,237 --> 00:49:57,720
Did you see the Chinese girl who accompanied Mr. Perm?

524
00:49:58,037 --> 00:49:59,098
I did.

525
00:49:59,283 --> 00:50:03,120
I thought you invited a dancer from Yaowarat to entertain us.

526
00:50:04,137 --> 00:50:05,360
Hey, they're here.

527
00:50:07,197 --> 00:50:08,198
Hello, ladies.

528
00:50:08,283 --> 00:50:09,284
(In unison) Hello, Perm.

529
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:13,521
I'd like to introduce your new friend.

530
00:50:14,080 --> 00:50:15,720
This is Shen, she is my wife.

531
00:50:16,600 --> 00:50:17,763
Can you hang out with all of you?

532
00:50:17,930 --> 00:50:19,300
I will be hanging out with the guys.

533
00:50:21,290 --> 00:50:22,360
See you on a dance floor.

534
00:50:27,603 --> 00:50:30,120
Too bad, we have no seat left for you.

535
00:50:31,710 --> 00:50:33,240
Why don't you find a chair?

536
00:50:34,457 --> 00:50:36,280
Or you can sit on the floor.

537
00:50:37,040 --> 00:50:39,280
Come on, Nuch.

538
00:50:39,641 --> 00:50:41,442
I will get a chair for you.

539
00:50:52,937 --> 00:50:53,938
Come here.

540
00:51:03,360 --> 00:51:04,361
Excuse me.

541
00:51:23,440 --> 00:51:25,750
What are your names?

542
00:51:26,041 --> 00:51:27,440
I only know Anongnuch.

543
00:51:28,760 --> 00:51:29,640
Call me by my full name.

544
00:51:30,423 --> 00:51:33,160
M.R. Anongnuch.

545
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:34,921
I'm sorry.

546
00:51:35,640 --> 00:51:37,400
M.R. Anongnuch.

547
00:51:40,310 --> 00:51:41,560
I'm Sriprapai.

548
00:51:41,670 --> 00:51:42,671
I'm Ornsalao.

549
00:51:42,957 --> 00:51:44,000
Amarapa.

550
00:51:44,223 --> 00:51:45,224
Saraithip.

551
00:51:45,360 --> 00:51:46,361
Chittamas.

552
00:51:46,597 --> 00:51:47,598
Wallapa.

553
00:51:48,970 --> 00:51:50,920
Let's test your skill in Thai.

554
00:51:51,590 --> 00:51:53,520
Can you memorize all of our six names?

555
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:59,160
Sriprapai, Ornsalao, Amarapa,

556
00:51:59,263 --> 00:52:02,000
Saraithip, Chittamas and Wallapa.

557
00:52:10,163 --> 00:52:11,280
Are you alright?

558
00:52:11,300 --> 00:52:12,301
I am alright. I can drink more.

559
00:52:12,601 --> 00:52:14,800
- Slow down.
- This is our second glass.

560
00:52:15,120 --> 00:52:16,440
Don't forget that we still need to dance.

561
00:52:17,221 --> 00:52:20,520
- How many glasses will we finish.
- I will wait. You go first.

562
00:52:21,130 --> 00:52:22,360
Right, I can't wait.

563
00:52:50,677 --> 00:52:51,678
It is time.

564
00:52:52,600 --> 00:52:55,200
I think you all have already had fun drinking already.

565
00:52:56,443 --> 00:52:58,640
It's time to enjoy the dance floor.

566
00:52:59,043 --> 00:53:00,240
If it's getting late,

567
00:53:00,463 --> 00:53:02,400
I don't think you all could be able to dance.

568
00:53:05,843 --> 00:53:07,040
I still can dance, can't you?

569
00:53:07,697 --> 00:53:08,698
Perm,

570
00:53:10,010 --> 00:53:12,880
can you dance with my daughter on my behalf?

571
00:53:13,337 --> 00:53:15,880
I'm too stiff, I can't dance with her.

572
00:53:16,457 --> 00:53:17,458
Can you take care of her?

573
00:53:17,623 --> 00:53:19,000
With my pleasure, Your Highness.

574
00:54:18,783 --> 00:54:19,920
I feel bad for her.

575
00:54:20,110 --> 00:54:22,500
Her husband didn't even want to dance with her.

576
00:54:22,577 --> 00:54:24,480
She is with her husband but she is left alone.

577
00:55:35,440 --> 00:55:36,441
Honey,

578
00:55:37,080 --> 00:55:39,000
when will you dance with me?

579
00:55:40,163 --> 00:55:41,920
Can't you see that I am dancing with Nuch?

580
00:55:44,250 --> 00:55:46,040
M.R. Anongnuch.

581
00:55:46,360 --> 00:55:47,920
Can I have my husband back?

582
00:55:48,070 --> 00:55:49,071
Hey!

583
00:55:49,370 --> 00:55:50,840
How could you say that to her?

584
00:55:51,640 --> 00:55:53,000
Where are your manners?

585
00:55:54,390 --> 00:55:55,560
You should wait for me outside.

586
00:55:56,840 --> 00:55:58,720
Get out, go.

587
00:56:05,657 --> 00:56:07,280
I'm sorry for her, please don't mind her.

588
00:57:18,897 --> 00:57:19,898
Ms. Shen,

589
00:57:21,877 --> 00:57:23,440
why are you sitting here all by yourself?

590
00:57:25,277 --> 00:57:26,278
What happened?

591
00:57:36,997 --> 00:57:37,998
Talk to me.

592
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:46,960
I was just bored of this stupid party.

593
00:57:48,797 --> 00:57:50,920
I think you should take me home.

594
00:57:51,440 --> 00:57:52,441
What about Mr. Perm?

595
00:57:55,210 --> 00:57:57,360
He is having fun with his peers inside.

596
00:57:57,750 --> 00:57:58,751
He must have forgotten about me.

597
00:57:59,797 --> 00:58:01,320
Can you take me home?

598
00:58:01,863 --> 00:58:03,360
And you can come back to give him a ride later.

599
00:58:04,570 --> 00:58:06,400
- But I…
- My husband said that

600
00:58:06,503 --> 00:58:08,000
you need to listen to me, didn't he?

601
00:58:12,663 --> 00:58:13,664
You're right.

602
00:58:17,840 --> 00:58:18,841
Ms. Shen.

603
00:58:20,350 --> 00:58:22,200
This is your favorite dance. It's waltz.

604
00:58:24,760 --> 00:58:26,880
Why don't you get back inside and dance for a song?

605
00:58:28,080 --> 00:58:29,320
Mr. Perm could be waiting for you.

606
00:58:39,520 --> 00:58:40,440
We can just dance here.

607
01:00:35,290 --> 01:00:36,403
I am just a driver.

608
01:00:37,110 --> 01:00:38,720
But I want you to know that

609
01:00:39,760 --> 01:00:41,360
I will always be here right by your side.

610
01:00:45,640 --> 01:00:46,641
What happened to you?

611
01:00:47,160 --> 01:00:49,840
I should have invited this unlucky woman into our house.
